    "id": "header"
   },
   "source": [
    "# {{ npc_name | json_inside }} \u2014 Unsloth Fine-Tune (Colab)\n",
    "\n",
    "**NPC:** {{ npc_name | json_inside }}  \n",
    "**Subject:** {{ subject | json_inside }}  \n",
    "**Model:** {{ model_name | json_inside }}  \n",
    "**Key:** {{ npc_key | json_inside }}\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "### Setup\n",
    "1. **Runtime -> Change runtime type** -> **T4 GPU**\n",
    "2. **Runtime -> Run all**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook will:\n",
    "1. Install Unsloth\n",
    "2. Load {{ model_name | json_inside }} in 4-bit\n",
    "3. Apply LoRA adapters\n",
    "4. Mount Google Drive and load the training dataset\n",
    "5. Run SFT training\n",
    "6. Export LoRA adapter to GGUF format (small file for Unity runtime loading)\n",
    "7. Save GGUF LoRA back to Google Drive for download"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "install"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%capture\nimport sys\n\nIN_COLAB = \"google.colab\" in sys.modules\n\nif IN_COLAB:\n    !pip install unsloth\n    !pip install huggingface_hub datasets trl\n    !pip install gguf  # required by convert_lora_to_gguf.py\nelse:\n    print(\"Not running in Colab; skipping install.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "model_header"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Unsloth\n",
    "Load the base model with 4-bit quantization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "load_model"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from unsloth import FastLanguageModel\nimport torch\n\nmax_seq_length = {{ max_seq_length | tojson }}\ndtype = None\nload_in_4bit = True\n\nmodel, tokenizer = FastLanguageModel.from_pretrained(\n    model_name = \"{{ model_name | json_inside }}\",\n    max_seq_length = max_seq_length,\n    dtype = dtype,\n    load_in_4bit = load_in_4bit,\n)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "lora_config"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = FastLanguageModel.get_peft_model(\n    model,\n    r = {{ lora_r | tojson }},\n    lora_alpha = {{ lora_alpha | tojson }},\n    lora_dropout = {{ lora_dropout | tojson }},\n    target_modules = [\"q_proj\", \"k_proj\", \"v_proj\", \"o_proj\",\n                      \"gate_proj\", \"up_proj\", \"down_proj\"],\n    use_gradient_checkpointing = \"{{ use_gradient_checkpointing | json_inside }}\",\n    random_state = {{ seed | tojson }},\n    max_seq_length = max_seq_length,\n)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "data_header"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Data Preparation\n",
    "Apply ChatML template and load the training dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "load_data"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "{{ data_loading_code | json_inside }}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "train_header"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Training\n",
    "Configure and run SFT training with Unsloth."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "train_config"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n\nper_device_train_batch_size = {{ per_device_train_batch_size | tojson }}\ngradient_accumulation_steps = {{ gradient_accumulation_steps | tojson }}\nmax_steps = {{ max_steps | tojson }}\nnum_train_epochs = {{ num_train_epochs | tojson }}\nlearning_rate = {{ learning_rate | tojson }}\nwarmup_steps = {{ warmup_steps | tojson }}\nweight_decay = {{ weight_decay | tojson }}\noptim = \"{{ optim | json_inside }}\"\nlr_scheduler_type = \"{{ lr_scheduler_type | json_inside }}\"\nseed = {{ seed | tojson }}\npacking = {{ 'True' if packing else 'False' }}\noutput_dir = \"{{ output_dir | json_inside }}\"\n\ngpu_stats = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0)\nstart_gpu_memory = round(torch.cuda.max_memory_reserved() / 1024 / 1024 / 1024, 3)\nmax_memory = round(gpu_stats.total_memory / 1024 / 1024 / 1024, 3)\nprint(f\"GPU = {gpu_stats.name}. Max memory = {max_memory} GB.\")\nprint(f\"{start_gpu_memory} GB of memory reserved.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "sft_trainer"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "{{ sft_trainer_code | json_inside }}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "train_on_responses"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from unsloth.chat_templates import train_on_responses_only\n\ntrainer = train_on_responses_only(\n    trainer,\n    instruction_part = \"<|im_start|>user\\n\",\n    response_part = \"<|im_start|>assistant\\n\",\n    tokenizer = tokenizer,\n)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "verify_masking"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Verify label masking works (check what % of tokens contribute to loss)\n# This manually masks instruction tokens to avoid depending on internal APIs.\nfor i, example in enumerate(dataset.select(range(2))):\n    tokenized = tokenizer(example[\"text\"], truncation=True, max_length=max_seq_length, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n    input_ids = tokenized.input_ids[0].clone()\n    labels = input_ids.clone()\n    # Mask everything before \"assistant\" (the instruction/user part)\n    text = example[\"text\"]\n    marker = \"<|im_start|>assistant\"\n    if marker in text:\n        pre = tokenizer(text[:text.index(marker)], truncation=True, max_length=max_seq_length)\n        labels[:len(pre.input_ids)] = -100\n    non_zero = (labels != -100).sum().item()\n    total = labels.numel()\n    print(f\"Example {i}: {non_zero}/{total} tokens contribute to loss ({100 * non_zero / total:.1f}%)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "train"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import time\ntrain_start = time.time()\n\ntrainer_stats = trainer.train()\n\ntrain_elapsed = time.time() - train_start\nprint(f\"\\nTraining completed in {train_elapsed / 60:.1f} minutes\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "train_stats"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "used_memory = round(torch.cuda.max_memory_reserved() / 1024 / 1024 / 1024, 3)\nused_memory_for_lora = round(used_memory - start_gpu_memory, 3)\nused_percentage = round(used_memory / max_memory * 1024, 3)\nlora_percentage = round(used_memory_for_lora / max_memory * 100, 3)\n\nprint(f\"Peak reserved memory = {used_memory} GB\")\nprint(f\"Peak reserved memory for training = {used_memory_for_lora} GB\")\nprint(f\"Peak reserved memory % of max = {used_percentage} %\")\nprint(f\"Peak reserved memory for training % of max = {lora_percentage} %\")"
   ]
  },
